        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 10:21PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1020 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marshall, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albion...              Marshall...            Battle Creek...
Brownlee Park...       Marengo...             Pine Creek...
Bedford...             Ceresco...             Duck Lake...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
